  "description": "A geographic classification based on the average annual minimum winter temperature. The USDA Plant Hardiness Zone Map divides North America into zones numbered 1 through 13, each subdivided into \"a\" and \"b\" halves. A plant's hardiness zone rating indicates the coldest zone in which it can survive winter.",
